# HURDAT2 data files are PINNED PROVENANCE — git must not rewrite their bytes.
#
# This repo is cloned with core.autocrlf=true on Windows, so without these rules git
# normalizes CRLF->LF on commit and re-expands on checkout. The records survive that,
# but the files stop being byte-identical to what NOAA served, and the checked-out
# bytes then differ per platform. For a dataset whose entire point is that a result
# can be reproduced later (NOAA *revises* HURDAT2 between releases), the bytes are
# the artifact. Mark them binary so git stores and restores them verbatim.
#
# Verify with:  sha256sum <f>  ==  git cat-file blob HEAD:<f> | sha256sum
hurdat2_atl.txt   -text
hurdat2_epac.txt  -text
HURDAT_full.csv   -text
HURDAT_atl.csv    -text
HURDAT_epac.csv   -text
